{"id":174,"idInBook":2571,"chapterId":10,"bookId":14,"arabic":"وَعَن أَبِي أَيُّوبَ: أَنَّ النَّبِيَّ صَلَّى اللَّهُ عَلَيْهِ وَسَلَّمَ كَانَ يَغْسِلُ رَأْسَهُ وَهُوَ مُحْرِمٌ","english":{"narrator":"","text":"Abu Ayyub said that the Prophet used to wash his head when he was in the sacred state.\n\nBukhari and Muslim."},"hadithNumber":2571,"hadithId":174,"reference":"10:174","meta":{"id":"mishkat_almasabih","length":4428,"totalChapters":25,"arabic":{"title":"مشكاة المصابيح","author":"الإمام الكاتب التبريزي"},"english":{"title":"Mishkat Al Masabih","author":"Al-Khatib Al-Tabrizi"}},"chapter":{"id":10,"bookId":14,"arabic":"كتاب المناسك","english":"The Rites of Pilgrimage","startHadith":2398,"endHadith":2643,"totalHadiths":246},"version":{"name":"mishkat_almasabih","title":"Mishkat Al Masabih","chapters":25}}